The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Sunday, April 8, 2007

 Poila Baisakh

 Usher in the Bengali New Year at The Telegraph Whirlpool Baisakh Utsav at Vidya Mandir, 6 pm.

 Easter Sunday

 Join an Easter procession, organised by churches of north Calcutta, from Duff Church to Holy Trinity Church, 4.30 pm to 5 pm.

 On Stage

 Catch Deshdrohi, directed by Moloy Roy Chowdhury, at Sisir Mancha as part of Sanglap Natyotsav, 6.30 pm.

 njoy Jaha Chai, directed by Rudraprasad Sengupta and Goutam Halder, at Girish Mancha, 6.30 pm.

 Kids Challenge

 Take your kids to Abacus and Brain Gym competition, presented by SIP Academy, at Netaji Indoor Stadium, 10 am to 4 pm.

 Show time

 Browse through an exhibition of works by Bageshree Dutta, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3 pm to 8 pm. 

 Go through Fawzan Hussains photographs at Seagull Arts and Media Resources Centre, 2 pm to 8 pm. 

 Drop in Spring Satchel, featuring crafts of rural Bengal, at Gallery Exposure, 3 pm to 8 pm. 

 Move on to a textile and jewellery show at Artisana, 10 am to 7.30 pm. 




